bio.experienceSummary:
I have many years of experience caring for children of all ages. I am looking to obtain part-time babysitting jobs in the afternoon, evenings and some weekends. I love to teach the children new things, do crafts, explore outside with them and most of all create amazing bonds.
 I want to be able to provide parents with comfort and security of having someone trustworthy watching their little ones.

Hello to all the parents here seeking care for your child. 

I have many years of caring for children of all ages. 

I also do date night child care for neighboring towns as well. 

My availability hours & days are listed here. 

Reach out to me here even if you just have a question about my schedule . 

Looking forward to hearing from you, 
Stacey

description.originalText: Stacey is playful and kind with kids. She took care of my son like family. I will highly recommend her for child care.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I'm a mother myself of two older girls, ages 26 and 24 both of which were preemies. I am extremely reliable, caring, and nurturing and will be sure to treat your children as if they were my own. I have just recently finished with a wonderful family that I have been with for about 3 years but the family is relocating out of state. Prior to having my own children, I worked in a pediatric office for five years. Feel free to leave a message for me with any questions you should have. Thank you.

description.displayText: Our family loves Lori!  We've been so lucky to have her with us for 2.5 years.  She is everything you'd want as a parent in a nanny - responsible, communicative, punctual, loving and caring.  She sees our kids as hers and treats them the same - reinforcing our schedules and house rules - a true extension of us when we're not there. We couldn't be happier to have found her.

bio.experienceSummary: I am 39 years old. I have nearly 15 years of daycare work experience-working with children ranging from 6 weeks to 6 years old. I also have 10 years of nanny work experience. I am a non-smoker. I have a clean driving record. I was First Aid and CPR trained for infants, children and adults and can renew it if needed. I love the outdoors, playing games and reading books. Arts and crafts are my specialty.

I am the mother of four grown children. I am interested in providing my services an expertise to assist parents in babysitting their own children. My genuine love and maternal instincts are truly an asset that any parent would appreciate from a caregiver to their loved one. 

I believe in positive reinforcing, challenge your child through conversation and games and yet being calm, patient and understanding.

I have also worked in the medical field for over 20 years, so my experience with handling all situations is another attribute that would help make parents extremely comfortable with me!

I am interested in 4 full days or 2 full days 8-10 hrs each. Sept 2025 looking forward to a new venture

description.displayText: There are many things I could say about Donna, but most importantly, we trust her with our three young children.  It was not easy for me to find someone I could say that about.  Donna is an experienced mother and has young grandchildren, so she knows what she is doing!  She is comfortable caring for children when they are sick, and is capable of making day to day decisions that are in their best interest.  My children love Donna, and are very comfortable with her and therefore so are we!  Donna is also VERY punctual.  Happy to discuss further by email or phone.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am a experienced loving childcare provider, and mother having 20 years of experience, not including raising my own two children (now 23 and 25 years old). Caring for and teaching children has always been my passion. I treat every child as if they were my own. I have worked as a nanny for multiple families, staying with each for three years or more, as well as working in preschools and daycares.

I provide engaging activities throughout the day, including coloring, reading, singing, and developmental play. My childcare includes teaching important milestones such as crawling, sitting up, walking, talking, and potty training. Weather permitting, I love to take children outside for walks, park visits, etc.

My experience includes caring for infants through elementary-aged children, which also includes twins and children with special needs. I provide patience, and loving care for each child's unique needs. I have excellent references from families I provided loving care for.
I have taught 32 years and I raised 4 children to be successful adults. I do not have CPR training but I have years of life experience.

The child I am with will be starting full-time school shortly. Ideally searching for a newborn/infant, as I am looking for longevity. I was also a PreK teacher in Metuchen for 4 years and a teacher's aide in the Edison school system for 17 years. I have nannied for over 10 years for 4 amazing families whose children have since started school. I'm a proud mom of 3 adult, well-rounded, successful children. I've also babysat for many families in the area. I am CPR and First Aide certified, Also, in my free time, I cook and deliver meals to several families in Metuchen.

description.originalText: If I could give more than 5 stars, I would. Tina is amazing. She is loving, caring and completely reliable. After taking care of our daughter for the past 2 years sheâ€™s now a member of our family. The next family that she works for will be so lucky.

bio.experienceSummary:
As a nurturing caregiver with nine years of experience, my passion lies in positively shaping young lives. I am patient, creative, and approachable, and I strive to create a safe and stimulating environment for children.

I believe in open communication with parents and regularly provide updates on their child's day. I adapt to each family's unique rules and routines to ensure consistency for the children in my care.

I enjoy a variety of games with kids, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational activities. My college education and CPR training further enhance my ability to provide quality care. I'm comfortable caring for up to three children of all ages.

Whether it's cooking meals, helping with carpools, or engaging in fun activities, I'm here to support families and bring joy to the children I care for. It would be my pleasure to be a part of your family's journey.

description.originalText: Melisa was an amazing nanny to my 3 yearold and 6 yearold sons. She took great care of them and was always on time for school dropoffs and pickups. She kept my younger child engaged with fun activities and helped my older one with schoolwork. Her kindness, reliability, and genuine care made us feel at ease, knowing our children were in great hands. I highly recommend Melisa to any family.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, I hope everyone is safe and healthy, I'm looking for an opportunities job for taking care of kids. I am available 3 times a week, ideally Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday. 

I am 33 years old, Childcare Specialist. I like to collaborate with children's growth and education. I'm responsible, patient, creative, active, and dedicated to child development. My biggest goal with children is to make sure they are safe and having fun. 

I was au pair for 2 years and I have 10 years of experiences, especially with babies and toddlers.
I have a degree in Physical Therapy and Certified Newborn Care Specialist. 

I am fully COVID vaccinated and also I am CPR certified.

I am looking forward to talk with you! Thank you.

description.originalText: Mariana worked with our family for the last 1.5 years, starting when my youngest was 5 months old. Over the last year, she watched my 6 year old son as well. I cannot recommend Mariana enough- she is patient, nurturing, and kind. She is an excellent communicator and works with the parents on ensuring we are all aligned on our approach for behavior, development, etc. Mariana is extremely proactive, often seeking out and recommending classes and activities. She prioritized socializing my younger son, creating a group of friends that he sees every day which was very important to us. I fully trust Mariana with both children's safety and know that she diligently watches them when they are out. Both of my children love Mariana and I could not recommend her more- we would have kept her with our family indefinitely if she was not moving!
